<h4 style="color: rgb(188, 32, 75); padding: 5px 0px; "><span style="font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;">APPS</span></h4>
  <dl>
    <dt>Which apps are included?</dt>
<dd>HelpMEwell (patient app – with 6 months of premium service) and Family-View.</dd>
<dt>What are the differences between the HelpMEwell and Family-View apps?</dt>
<dd>HelpMEwell is the patient logging app, and Family-View is for the adult children of the patient to view their parent's logged data, recieve alerts, and provide encouragement.</dd>
<dt>What is the Plus service about?</dt>
<dd>It’s a service related to the alerts and alarms.</dd>
<dt>Which phones and tablets work with Family-View? Will this app be available for iPad?</dt>
<dd>The Family-View apps will run on any iOS device that can run iOS7 or higher. That includes iPad 4, iPad air, and all iPad mini. It works with all the iPhones from the 4S to the newest ones. It also works with iPod touch 5th generation. Moreover our web-based version works with the Android systems from version 4.4 on up, as long as they have internet connectivity.</dd>
</dl>

<h4 style="color: rgb(188, 32, 75); padding: 5px 0px; "><span style="font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;">BUY ONE GIVE ONE</span></h4>
<dl><span style="font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;">
<dt>Am I eligible for a free HelpMEwell app for my parent? Is there a partnership or scholarship program for adults with chronic disease?</dt>
<dd>We will give the donated HelpMEwell and Family-View apps to the (TBD) foundation that will be responsible for distributing them to people in need. Please make sure to contact them to discover the eligibility criteria.</dd>
